The output will look like this:

You'll not get any output in the notebook. `file=open(txt,"a")` redirects all the output to the file named `txt`. So, search for `txt` named file. That will be a shell file.
The output will look like this:
```
python label_image.py --image=9733.jpg --input_height=299 --input_width=299 --graph=retrained_graph.pb --labels=retrained_labels.txt  --input_layer="Mul" --output_layer="final_result"

```
